So%20when%20I%20found%20out%20there%20was%20a%20job%20for%20that%2C%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Lauren%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20as%20a%20face%20painter%20at%20an%20amusement%20park%20and%20makeup%20artist%20at%20Sephora%2C%20said.%20Since%20scoring%20her%20full-time%20job%20following%20the%20College%20Program%2C%20she's%20amassed%20more%20than%20one%20million%20TikTok%20followers%20by%20explaining%20how%20she%20broke%20in%20and%20using%20humor%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20what%20working%20for%20the%20company%20is%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren's%20job%20falls%20within%20Disney's%20parks%20division%20(which%20also%20encompasses%20merchandise%20and%20cruises)%2C%20sitting%20alongside%20entertainment%20and%20ESPN%2C%20its%20two%20other%20main%20branches.%20Disney%20employs%20more%20than%20200%2C000%20people%20worldwide%2C%20but%20joining%20its%20global%20workforce%20in%20this%20volatile%20climate%20might%20seem%20tougher%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20tightened%20its%20belt%20this%20year%2C%20reducing%20headcount%20by%208%2C000%20roles%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbob-iger-ceo-disney-return-insiders-anxious-losing-faith-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECEO%20Bob%20Iger%20set%20out%20to%20cut%20costs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%247.5%20billion.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20entertainment%20industry%20contracted%20in%202023%20by%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20jobs%2C%20leaving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-assistant-career-challenges-moving-up-hollywood-stalling-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emany%20young%20people%20feeling%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20blocked%20from%20breaking%20into%20Hollywood%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fassistants-netflix-disney-warner-bros-discovery-hollywood-cant-get-promotions-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadvancing%20their%20careers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20many%20entry-level%20and%20early-career%20workers%20who%20want%20a%20job%20in%20entertainment%2C%20whether%20that's%20on%20the%20screen%20or%20in%20live%20experiences%2C%20Disney's%20global%20reach%2C%20iconic%20IP%2C%20and%20storytelling%20legacy%20make%20it%20a%20coveted%20place%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Green%2C%20director%20of%20the%20master%20of%20entertainment%20industry%20management%20program%20at%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University's%20Heinz%20College%2C%20said%20a%20job%20at%20Disney%20can%20set%20Hollywood%20workers%20up%20for%20bright%20futures.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20positive%20thing%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20their%20hiring%20policy%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20such%20a%20well-known%20brand.%26quot%3B%20Green%20interned%20at%20Disney%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20handling%20tasks%20like%20script%20coverage%20(summarizing%20screenplays%20for%20creative%20executives)%2C%20and%20a%20number%20of%20his%20students%20have%20landed%20jobs%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20can%20Disney%20hopefuls%20break%20in%3F%20To%20demystify%20the%20interview%20process%20and%20some%20of%20the%20techniques%20Disney%20uses%20to%20assess%20prospective%20hires%2C%20BI%20spoke%20to%20six%20current%20and%20former%20Disney%20employees%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20experts%20familiar%20with%20entertainment-industry%20recruiting.%20Most%20company%20sources%20requested%20anonymity%20because%20they%20were%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20with%20reporters.%20Spokespersons%20for%20Disney%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20about%20recruiting%20practices%20or%20how%20many%20people%20apply%20and%20are%20hired%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sources%20agreed%20that%20the%20hiring%20experience%20varies%20widely%20depending%20on%20the%20division%20and%20role%20in%20question.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20process%20of%20landing%20a%20staff%20job%20in%20the%20parks%20would%20be%20quite%20distinct%20from%20a%20position%20at%20a%20Disney-owned%20network%20or%20studio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20people%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0primarily%20junior-%20and%20early-career%20staffers%20in%20roles%20ranging%20from%20tech%20and%20engineering%20to%20television%20and%20creative%20development%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0added%20that%20Disney%20looks%20for%20candidates%20whose%20skills%20match%20the%20role's%20needs%20and%20who%20are%20problem-solvers.%20The%20company%20also%20wants%20to%20bring%20on%20employees%20who%20have%20a%20connection%20to%20its%20history%2C%20products%2C%20and%20DNA%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20recruiting%20process%20aims%20to%20draw%20that%20out%2C%20and%20what%20candidates%20should%20prepare%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%20one%3A%20Meet%20a%20recruiter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20applying%20online%20for%20an%20open%20role%2C%20connecting%20with%20an%20official%20recruiter%20for%20the%20company%20is%20generally%20the%20first%20step%20in%20Disney's%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20said%20there%20are%20many%20different%20kinds%20of%20recruiters%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0some%20focus%20on%20entertainment%2C%20she%20said%2C%20while%20others%20specialize%20in%20filling%20part-%20or%20full-time%20roles.%20Still%20others%20focus%20on%20the%20Disney%20College%20Program.%20Some%20can%20help%20you%20figure%20out%20where%20in%20the%20company%20you're%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20successful%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecruiters%20have%20significant%20sway%20over%20how%20the%20interview%20process%20unfolds%2C%20including%20who%20advances%20and%20who%20gets%20nixed.%20According%20to%20one%20Disney%20employee%20hired%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20managers%20may%20tell%20recruiters%20the%20particulars%20they're%20seeking%20in%20candidates.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20the%20hiring%20manager%20will%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%20is%20exactly%20what%20I%20want%2C'%26quot%3B%20this%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20how%20many%20rounds%20applicants%20will%20go%20through%20and%20the%20tone%20and%20tenor%20of%20the%20interviews%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20really%20depends%20on%20the%20position%20and%20really%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20hiring%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20second%20current%20employee%2C%20who%20works%20in%20a%20technology-related%20function%2C%20recalled%20having%20two%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20first%20with%20the%20person%20who%20is%20now%20their%20boss%2C%20and%20the%20second%20with%20both%20a%20senior%20technology%20staffer%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20employee's%20current%20team.%20The%20first%20interview%20was%20to%20determine%20whether%20this%20person%20was%20a%20cultural%20fit%20for%20the%20company%2C%20while%20the%20second%20was%20more%20technical%2C%20testing%20the%20candidate's%20mastery%20of%20skills%20required%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidates%20who%20don't%20receive%20an%20offer%20shouldn't%20be%20discouraged%2C%20Lauren%20said.%20Instead%2C%20she%20advised%20them%20to%20seek%20recruiters'%20guidance%20about%20other%20opportunities.%20Recently%2C%20she%20applied%20for%20a%20cosmetology%20job%20in%20the%20parks%2C%20but%20the%20prospective%20transfer%20didn't%20work%20out.%20Still%2C%20she's%20not%20giving%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20gave%20her%20feedback%20on%20where%20she%20could%20develop%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0she%20hasn't%20had%20much%20experience%20cutting%20hair%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20she%20can%20try%20again%20in%20a%20few%20months%20or%20explore%20options%20in%20costuming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRejection%20is%20redirection%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20kind%20of%20more%20like%2C%20'Not%20now%2C%20but%20maybe%20later.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterview%20questions%20tap%20into%20candidates'%20skills%20and%20Disney%20knowledge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20role%2C%20candidates%20could%20face%20numerous%20interview%20rounds%2C%20ranging%20from%20two%20or%20three%20up%20to%20five%20or%20six.%20The%20process%20includes%20personal%20and%20behavioral%20questions%20that%20assess%20your%20qualitative%20aptitude%20for%20the%20job%20and%20how%20well%20you%20understand%20Disney's%20culture%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20would%20ask%20me%2C%20'What%20are%20your%20hobbies%3F'%20or%20'What%20were%20some%20of%20your%20classes%20while%20you%20were%20in%20school%3F'%20And%20then%20they'd%20be%20like%3A%20'Hey%2C%20do%20you%20have%20experience%20with%20Adobe%20Photoshop%3F'%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20first%20employee.%20The%20recruiters'%20goal%2C%20this%20person%20continued%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20make%20sure%20this%20person%20can%20not%20only%20say%20they%20know%20how%20to%20use%20a%20language%20or%20know%20how%20to%20use%20a%20specific%20tool%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20can%20you%20give%20me%20an%20example%20of%20how%20they'd%20use%20that%20tool%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20employee%20went%20through%20the%20Disney%20College%20Program%20and%20said%20applicants%20for%20that%20program%20should%20expect%20to%20take%20personality%20assessments%20with%20automatically-scored%20multiple%20choice%20questions%20that%20can%20disqualify%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuestions%20could%20address%20topics%20like%20how%20applicants%20would%20interact%20with%20guests%20or%20whether%20they're%20problem%20solvers%20in%20their%20everyday%20lives%2C%20according%20to%20this%20person.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20candidate%20might%20be%20asked%20to%20select%20from%20one%20of%20several%20ways%20they%20could%20address%20a%20complicated%20situation%20with%20parks%20goers%2C%20the%20person%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20sources%20highlighted%20one%20question%20in%20particular%20as%20critical%3A%20Why%20do%20you%20want%20to%20work%20for%20Disney%3F%20This%20question%20can%20give%20rise%20to%20others%2C%20like%3A%20What's%20your%20favorite%20Disney%20park%3F%20What's%20your%20favorite%20ride%3F%20Sources%20concerned%20with%20entertainment-related%20roles%20said%20recruiters%20might%20ask%20candidates%20to%20name%20a%20few%20shows%20they've%20recently%20watched.%20A%20compelling%20answer%20connecting%20candidates%20to%20the%20ethos%20of%20the%20Mouse%20House%20can%20give%20them%20an%20edge%2C%20the%20people%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20Lauren's%20early%20conversations%20with%20recruiters%2C%20this%20question%20came%20up%20almost%20immediately%2C%20she%20said.%20Recruiters%2C%20she%20added%2C%20want%20to%20establish%20that%20candidates%20are%20%26quot%3Bpassionate%20about%20the%20company%20first%20and%20foremost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20answer%2C%20Lauren%20invoked%20themes%20from%20her%20childhood%2C%20she%20said%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20loving%20storytelling%20and%20wanting%20to%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20happiness%20for%20other%20people.%26quot%3B%20The%20second%20employee%20(who%20works%20in%20a%20tech-related%20function)%C2%A0recalled%20connecting%20their%20upbringing%20as%20a%20first-generation%20immigrant%20to%20the%20role%20Disney%20stories%20and%20characters%20played%20in%20helping%20them%20better%20integrate%20into%20US%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20candidates%20looking%20to%20work%20in%20Disney's%20entertainment%20division%2C%20a%20question%20Green%20and%20other%20experts%20mentioned%20is%3A%20What%20are%20you%20watching%20on%20television%20and%20streaming%20right%20now%3F%20The%20first%20employee%20said%20they%20mentioned%20ABC's%20%26quot%3BGrey's%20Anatomy%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20favorite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20absolutely%20appropriate%20to%20have%20something%20in%20your%20back%20pocket%20on%20Hulu%20and%20Disney%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20just%20as%20important%20to%20know%20what%20you're%20watching%20on%20other%20streamers%20or%20network%20television%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%20And%2C%20he%20advised%2C%20don't%20just%20lean%20on%20obvious%20choices%3A%20%26quot%3B'Succession'%20is%20low-hanging%20fruit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPractical%20assessments%20test%20competencies%20and%20problem-solving%20skills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPractical%20assessments%20that%20determine%20how%20comfortable%20candidates%20would%20be%20in%20tackling%20the%20qualitative%20elements%20of%20their%20would-be%20jobs%20are%20a%20hallmark%20of%20Disney%20interviews%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%20said%20some%20of%20his%20students%20had%20been%20asked%20to%20complete%20PowerPoint%20presentations%2C%20script%20coverage%20assignments%2C%20or%20data%20analysis%20using%20figures%20provided%20by%20the%20company%20in%20order%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20chops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Lauren%20was%20in%20the%20running%20for%20her%20current%20job%2C%20she%20said%2C%20recruiters%20asked%20her%20to%20explain%20how%20she'd%20correct%20or%20enhance%20a%20series%20of%20photos%20%E2%80%94%20from%20improving%20brightness%20to%20fixing%20the%20contrast%20or%20saturation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Ban%20artistic%20eye%20to%20see%20where%20the%20creative%20aspect%20would%20come%20into%20play.%26quot%3B%20Recruiters%20used%20open-ended%20questions%20to%20avoid%20guiding%20her%20to%20particular%20answers%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%2C%20tech-focused%20employee%20remembers%20encountering%20a%20coding%20problem%20during%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20of%20those%20coding%20questions%20that%20seem%20very%20small%20but%20can%20easily%20have%20gotchas%26quot%3B%20that%20candidates%20might%20not%20catch%20on%20first%20glance%2C%20said%20this%20person.%20%26quot%3BThey%20gave%20me%20a%20prompt%20that%20I%20had%20to%20fill%20in%2C%20either%20in%20Java%20or%20in%20pseudocode%2C%20and%20then%20they%20asked%20me%3A%20'Okay%2C%20imagine%20that%20this%20was%20not%20the%20prompt%20or%20that%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20prompt%20was%20a%20little%20broader.%20How%20would%20you%20improve%20what%20you've%20written%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20current%20employee%2C%20a%20creative%20assistant%20in%20Disney's%20entertainment%20division%2C%20recalled%20being%20tested%20on%20their%20competency%20in%20assessing%20creative%20work%2C%20namely%20doing%20script%20coverage.%20%26quot%3BThey%20simply%20ask%20for%20a%20script%20to%20be%20read%20%E2%80%94%20they%20gave%20ample%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20write%20coverage%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20this%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%2C%20this%20assistant%20explained%2C%20was%20for%20their%20future%20bosses%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20whether%20they%20can%20summarize%20ideas%20clearly%20and%20concisely%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20critical%20for%20a%20development%20role.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECuriosity%20counts%20%E2%80%94%20about%20the%20role%2C%20the%20company%2C%20the%20industry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20encouraged%20candidates%20to%20be%20curious%20and%20raise%20their%20own%20questions%20with%20recruiters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20White%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20recruiting%20expert%20who's%20studied%20the%20company's%20interviewing%20processes%20and%20assembled%20videos%20about%20getting%20hired%20there%20on%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fapp%3Ddesktop%26v%3Dm8Y_SzNgobE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%20channel%2C%20Ben%20Talks%20Talent%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0suggested%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20needs%20to%20happen%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20for%20you%20to%20consider%20this%20to%20be%20a%20successful%20hire%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20proposed%20asking%20about%20training%20and%20onboarding%2C%20to%20show%20that%20a%20candidate's%20outlook%20on%20the%20job%20is%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20you're%20looking%20for%2C%20'What%20do%20I%20need%20to%20do%20to%20win%20for%20you%20to%20and%20to%20be%20a%2